        <section class="box">
            <h1>Resolving Blue Screen errors in ImpendingMoon</h1>
            <p>
                Blue screen errors (also called <em>vibe checks, STOP button errors, stream errors, or OUCH errors</em>)
                can occur if a serious problem causes ImpendingMoon to shut down or restart the stream unexpectedly to
                protect himself from embarrassment. You might see a message that says, "The broadcast you are watching
                has ended" or a similar message.
            </p>
            <p>
                A rogue chat message, bodged ethernet cable, or the terrible code Moon writes might have caused this
                error. To help determine the cause, the blue screen error might display a STOP code, such as
                ROSS_HAS_ESCAPED. When it's available, the name of the scene that was being broadcast is also listed
                after "What failed:".
            </p>
        </section>
        <section class="box">
            <h2>Basic Troubleshooting Steps for Blue Screen Errors</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>Remove any new items.</strong> If you added a new input, widget, or OBS plugin, try
                    disabling it and restarting the stream.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Start the stream in emote-only mode.</strong>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Check the Channel Manager.</strong>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Check for sufficient free space on the hard drive.</strong>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Install the latest OBS Updates.</strong>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Restore ImpendingMoon.</strong>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
        <section class="box">
            <h2>Advanced Troubleshooting Steps for Blue Screen Errors</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>Check the VOD.</strong>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Run the Memory Diagnostics Tool.</strong>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Take a Nap.</strong> Just go to sleep.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
